@*
    In-sheet unit-conversion prompt for the recipe ingredient editor (C10 early UX, plantry-c9s2).

    Shown when the author picks a cross-dimension unit (e.g. "cup" for a product catalogued in "g"):
    the Alpine $watch on draft.unitId detects the gap live via OnGetCheckConversionAsync and sets
    draft.needsConversion = true. This partial renders the inline ask, styled as an informational prompt
    (not an error).

    Framing follows Option 1 (agreed in .preview/recipe-conversion-prompt-options.html):
      "Plantry stocks {ProductName} in {defaultUnitCode}. How much is 1 {fromUnitCode}?"
      1 {fromUnitCode} = [ input ] {defaultUnitCode}
      Saved to your catalog — you only set this once, and every future recipe reuses it.
      [Measure in {defaultUnitCode} instead]

    Alpine contract (reads from the host's draft object):
      draft.needsConversion     — controls x-if on the outer template (DOM is truly absent when false,
                                   so strict-mode Playwright locators never find the hidden input)
      draft.productName         — product display name (e.g. "Flour")
      draft.unitId              — the chosen from-unit id
      draft.defaultUnitId       — the product's default unit id
      draft.defaultUnitCode     — the product's default unit code (e.g. "g")
      draft.conversionFactor    — two-way bound to the factor input
      unitLabel(id)             — host helper: unitId → code string (e.g. "cup")

    Why x-if (template) not x-show:
      - x-show renders the div but hides it with CSS. Playwright strict-mode locator("input[type='number']")
        finds ALL DOM inputs including hidden ones, breaking existing E2E tests that expect exactly one
        number input in the sheet.
      - x-if on a <template> only inserts the child elements when truthy — the input is genuinely absent
        from the DOM when draft.needsConversion is false, keeping the E2E locators unambiguous.

    The "Measure in {default} instead" escape sets draft.unitId = draft.defaultUnitId, which clears
    the $watch trigger and removes this block from the DOM.
*@

<template x-if="draft.needsConversion">
    <div style="margin-top:var(--space-4);padding:var(--space-3) var(--space-4);background:var(--color-surface-2);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:var(--radius-md)">
        <p style="margin:0 0 var(--space-1);font-size:var(--font-size-sm)">
            Plantry stocks <strong x-text="draft.productName"></strong> in <strong x-text="draft.defaultUnitCode"></strong>.
            How much is 1 <span x-text="unitLabel(draft.unitId)"></span>?
        </p>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:var(--space-2);margin-bottom:var(--space-2);flex-wrap:wrap">
            <span style="font-size:var(--font-size-sm)">1 <span x-text="unitLabel(draft.unitId)"></span> =</span>
            <input type="number" class="field__input" step="any" min="0"
                   placeholder="e.g. 120"
                   x-model="draft.conversionFactor"
                   style="width:8rem" />
            <span style="font-size:var(--font-size-sm)" x-text="draft.defaultUnitCode"></span>
        </div>
        <p style="margin:0 0 var(--space-2);font-size:var(--font-size-sm);color:var(--color-text-muted)">
            Saved to your catalog — you only set this once, and every future recipe reuses it.
        </p>
        <button type="button"
                class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm"
                @@click="draft.unitId = draft.defaultUnitId; draft.needsConversion = false; draft.conversionFactor = ''">
            Measure in <span x-text="draft.defaultUnitCode"></span> instead
        </button>
    </div>
</template>
